remarks.para:
Calling the  method with a specific text string is equivalent to: 


calling  to get a  object;

calling the  object's  method with the same text string;

calling SpeakFormatted with the  object.

Calling the  method with a specific text string is equivalent to: 


calling  to get a  object;

calling the   object's  method with the same text string;

calling ThinkFormatted with the  object.

When SuspendPause is True and the user switches away from your application:


the character's request queue is paused;

the current animation (if any) is paused;

the current speech output (if any) is paused;

the current word balloon output (if any) is paused;

 Listening mode is paused (if it's active).



Immediate prepares are not paused.

 When the user switches back to your application, everything that was paused is resumed.

When SuspendStop is True and the user switches away from your application:


the character's request queue is stopped, except for queued prepares;

the current animation (if any) is stopped;

the current speech output (if any) is stopped;

the current word balloon output (if any) is stopped;

 Listening mode is stopped (if it's active).



Queued and immediate prepares are not stopped.

When SuspendHide is True and the user switches away from your application:


the character window is hidden, if it's visible and not contained;

the word balloon is hidden, if it's visible;

the Listening tip is hidden, if it's visible;

the Voice Commands window is hidden, if it's visible.

 When the user switches back to your application, everything that was hidden is shown again.
